lead_paragraph: Dr. Quentin Young, a longtime health advocate who served as a personal physician to Martin Luther King during the civil rights leader's stay in Chicago, died Monday at age 92.

headline.main: Dr. Quentin Young, Longtime Health Advocate, Dies at 92
